2. `isBoomerangHelper(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, direction, count)`: This function checks if the current point (x1, y1) is on the correct side of the line passing through (x2, y2) and (x3, y3) with direction `direction` (0 for left, 1 for right). If the function returns true, then the current point is on the correct side of the line, and we can continue the recursion.
3. `isBoomerangHelper(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, direction, count)`: This function checks if the current point (x1, y1) is on the correct side of the line passing through (x2, y2) and (x3, y3) with direction `direction` (0 for left, 1 for right). If the function returns true, then the current point is on the correct side of the line, and we can continue the recursion.

